    ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:1:{s:27:"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom";a:8:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:23:"Welcome Brandon Keepers";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:0:"";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"href";s:61:"http://orderedlist.com/blog/articles/welcome-brandon-keepers/";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:2:"id";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:61:"http://orderedlist.com/blog/articles/welcome-brandon-keepers/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"updated";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"2011-01-03T11:47:09-05:00";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:9:"published";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:25:"2010-12-14T09:59:00-05:00";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"summary";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:129:"<p>We&#8217;re growing again, and thrilled to announce that Brandon is officially the fourth member of the Ordered List team.</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"content";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1092:"<p>We&#8217;re growing again, and thrilled to announce that Brandon is officially the fourth member of the Ordered List team.</p><p>We&#8217;ve been working with Brandon for years, while he worked at <a href="http://collectiveidea.com">Collective Idea</a>, on various client and side projects. When we learned <a href="http://opensoul.org/blog/archives/2010/12/02/leaving-collective-idea/">he was leaving</a>, we jumped at the chance to work with him full time. And to our excitement, he accepted and starts on January 3rd, 2011.</p>
<p class="photo"><img src="http://orderedlist.com/assets/4d0785bbdabe9d78870000f7/article_full_width/brandon.jpg" title="Brandon Keepers" alt="Brandon Keepers" /></p>
<p>Brandon has some serious Ruby and JavaScript chops, and will be helping us better serve our clients, build out new <a href="http://get.harmonyapp.com">Harmony</a> features, and push our open source software forward. He also has a keen eye for design, and a firm attention to detail. We couldn&#8217;t be more excited to have Brandon join the team. It&#8217;s going to be a great 2011!</p>";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:4:"type";s:4:"html";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:6:"author";a:1:{i:0;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:16:"
        
